modules.description: This module implements GPU-accelerated 2D rendering operations using OpenGL ES 2.0, including texture management, path filling/stroking, and triangle rendering. It works with vector graphics primitives like paths, vertex buffers, and paint styles, along with low-level GL resources. Concrete use cases include rendering UI elements with antialiased edges, dynamic texture updates for sprites or text, and efficient batched drawing of complex shapes using shaders.

This module enables high-performance 2D rendering using OpenGL ES 2.0, focusing on vector graphics and GPU-accelerated operations. It provides data types for paths, vertex buffers, paint styles, and textures, along with operations for filling and stroking paths, rendering triangles, and managing GL resources. You can use it to draw smooth UI elements, update textures dynamically for sprites or text, and batch complex shape rendering through custom shaders.
